The paper deals with the stable marriage problem, which is a classic topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The concept of popular matchings is related to social choice theory and voting systems, which are also studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the study of polytopes, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and combinatorics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of decision problems, which is a common theme in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
